   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-1" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-a" mid="48" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="7"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>No matter how strong the thieves are, the Alicantos are never a force to be looked down on. That's why the former Presidents avoided any clash with the Alicantos too.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-b" mid="50" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="8"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>There must be a reason why the Alicantos became slaves. If we find the reason, maybe it will be helpful in freeing the Alicantos.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-c" mid="51" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="9"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>From what I heard, an Alicanto survivor seems to be hiding in the <FONT color=#a82424>Cradle of the Abandoned</FONT>.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-2" mid="52" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Sure, I'll do that.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="10"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>Can you please meet him and find out how the Alicantos were forced into slavery?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1878_weak_alicanto-1" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_question mid="77"><![CDATA[<html>$Weak Alicanto$<BR>(Coughs badly) Looking back, my life is full of regrets...</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-2" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_question mid="11"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>The <FONT color=#a82424>Alicanto</FONT> at the <FONT color=#a82424>Cradle of the Abandoned</FONT> must be very weak by now. Please don't be too surprised even when he doesn't look like what you expected.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1878_weak_alicanto-2" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1878_weak_alicanto-2-a" mid="54" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Explain the details)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="12"><![CDATA[<html>$Weak Alicanto$<BR>Who... who are you...? (Coughs) How... do you... know me...?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1878_weak_alicanto-2-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1878_weak_alicanto-2-b" mid="55" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="13"><![CDATA[<html>$Weak Alicanto$<BR>Hahaha... So there still are people who's concerned about a tribe that even its own leader had forsaken.<BR><FONT color=#7e12d2>(You can see sad shades of regret in the Alicanto's eyes.)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1878_weak_alicanto-2-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1878_weak_alicanto-2-c" mid="56" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="14"><![CDATA[<html>$Weak Alicanto$<BR>Yeah... those spiteful thieves... they should be gnawed on alive... They approached my tribe with fake smiles and offered the <FONT color=#a82424>fake goldstone</FONT> to us.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1878_weak_alicanto-2-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1878_weak_alicanto-2-d" mid="57" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="15"><![CDATA[<html>$Weak Alicanto$<BR>The pricy jewel <FONT color=#a82424>Goldstone Elixirs</FONT> were nothing but inedible rocks to us. Our main source of food came from the normal goldstones that were mainly used for making the liquor.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1878_weak_alicanto-2-d" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1878_weak_alicanto-2-e" mid="58" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="16"><![CDATA[<html>$Weak Alicanto$<BR>The thieves said they were merchants who only traded Goldstone Elixirs and offered to provide all the normal goldstones that they gained from mining. There was no reason for us to reject such an offer since it meant we didn't have to trouble ourselves in mining the goldstones anymore.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1878_weak_alicanto-2-e" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1878_weak_alicanto-2-f" mid="59" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="17"><![CDATA[<html>$Weak Alicanto$<BR>However... my tribesmen who ate what they gave us soon died one by one. The fake goldstone was addictive, and we couldn't stop eating them even when we knew we would end up dead... Krrgh...</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1878_weak_alicanto-2-f" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1878_weak_alicanto-2-g" mid="60" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Merca didn't help you at all?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="18"><![CDATA[<html>$Weak Alicanto$<BR>When my tribe fell weak, the thieves took over our mines and started enslaving my tribesmen using the fake goldstone as a bait!! We... we had to mine until our nails wore out just to eat a tiny piece of goldstone!!</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1878_weak_alicanto-2-g" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1878_weak_alicanto-2-h" mid="62" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Ah…….</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="19"><![CDATA[<html>$Weak Alicanto$<BR><FONT color=#a82424>Merca</FONT> sent an army for us. However, it was hard for them to fight the thieves who knew the terrains better, and eventually it seemed like they were not willing to withstand any more losses to save the Alicantos.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1878_weak_alicanto-2-h" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1878_weak_alicanto-2-i" mid="64" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="20"><![CDATA[<html>$Weak Alicanto$<BR>For Merca, sieging a few mines from the thieves to mine them on their own provided similar yields to mining a small amount of goldstones under our approval.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1878_weak_alicanto-2-i" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1878_weak_alicanto-2-j" mid="65" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="21"><![CDATA[<html>$Weak Alicanto$<BR>That's life. Though I didn't get addicted to the fake goldstone, I was fatally injured in an uprising... All I want is to end the suffering of the Alicantos.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1878_weak_alicanto-2-j" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1878_weak_alicanto-2-k" mid="66" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="22"><![CDATA[<html>$Weak Alicanto$<BR>Please tell <FONT color=#a82424>Pero</FONT> that even though we know that the fake goldstone is the reason for slavery, the Alicantos are already addicted and there's no cure. It would be better to let my tribesmen rest in peace than let them carry on a life strung out on fake goldstone.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1878_weak_alicanto-2-k" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1878_weak_alicanto-3" mid="67" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="23"><![CDATA[<html>$Weak Alicanto$<BR>Please show mercy to those who can't keep their dignity despite their wishes and let them rest in peace. All hopes were already lost the moment the foolish man who was not fit to be called our leader abandoned his own people and ran away...</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1878_weak_alicanto-3" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_question mid="24"><![CDATA[<html>$Weak Alicanto$<BR>It's just an end of an era… The end of the era when Alicantos ruled the Broken Goldstone Canyon...</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-3" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-3-a" mid="69" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Tell him what the Alicanto said.)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="25"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>You're back. Did you manage to talk to the Alicanto survivor?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-3-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-3-b" mid="70" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="26"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>The entire tribe has been addicted and there's no cure... So all he wants is for them to rest in peace…?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-3-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-3-c" mid="71" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(I knew he would be dejected...)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="27"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>I see... Their leader's long gone and I believe there aren't many survivors anymore too, and if all of them are addicted... There's nothing we can do.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-3-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-3-d" mid="73" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="28"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>Just like he said, the rise and fall of tribes and countries must be a natural phenomenon.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-3-d" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-3-e" mid="74" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="29"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>Thank you for all you've done, <FONT color=#387206>{user_nick}</FONT>. I'm sorry to bring your spirits down too.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-3-e" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-3-f" mid="75" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html><FONT color=#086171>(Receive Reward)</FONT></html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="30"><![CDATA[<html>$Quest Reward$</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-3-f" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-3-!next" mid="76" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="31"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>If you don't mind, can you help me for the last time and fulfill the Alicanto and my wish?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
